iences     View Menu  Down arrow icon               Creating and transforming information in the healthcare industry   Biomedical and health information science isn’t just creating information—it’s turning that information into applicable knowledge and improving healthcare delivery. Our Department of Biomedical and Health Information Sciences prepares you for cutting-edge roles at the forefront of the healthcare arena.  Our innovative curriculum incorporates the newest ideas and technology, and constantly evolves to make sure our students leave prepared for positions as leaders in their field. Located in the heart of the Illinois Medical District, our students have access to clinical sites, professional associations, state-of-the-art facilities and a top-notch faculty with research expertise and real-world industry experience.    Stats and Facts      #2    U.S. News & World Report ranks our online bachelor's in health information management No. 2 among bachelor's programs with the highest six-year graduation rates                 Our MS in biomedical visualization is the    2nd              oldest program of its kind and one of only    4              accredited graduate programs in North America                1st    Our online master's in health informatics is the first online graduate program accredited by the Commission on Accreditation for Health Informatics and Information Management Education                    Biomedical Visualization Programs  With a curriculum at the leading edge of science and technology, our Biomedical Visualization Master of Science program attracts students from diverse disciplines, such as biology, art, computer science, and the health/clinical sciences.   Request information       Name  Type  Description  Apply       Minor in Life Science Visualization   On Campus  Harness digital media technology to create dynamic works of art that advance understanding   Apply      MS in Biomedical Visualization   On Campus  Candidates who are strong in science and have excellent art skills can become experts in the visual communication of complex medical and scientific concepts   Apply            Biomedical and Health Informatics Program  Our PhD in biomedical and health informatics prepares future academicians and healthcare industry leaders. We emphasize interdisciplinary, collaborative research and mentorship, developing scholars who solve complex knowledge management issues in healthcare.   Request information       Name  Type  Description  Apply       PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics   On Campus  For people with a passion for health information. Prepare to advance the discovery and application of new ideas in health information technology   Apply            Health Informatics Programs  Satisfy your interests in technology, health and research with a degree in health informatics. As clinicians become more reliant on information technology, the demand for health informaticians continues to grow. Graduates of our online Health Informatics programs are ready to lead their organizations in the use of technology strategies to improve patient care and safety.   Request information       Name  Type  Description  Apply       MS in Health Informatics   Online  Become an expert in linking information technology and communications to improve the quality and safety of patient care   Apply      Post-Master’s Certificate in Health Informatics   Online  Our students enter with advanced degrees and work experience, and leave as trained informaticians ready to make an impact on the healthcare industry   Apply      Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Informatics   Online  Designed to provide experienced health care and IT professionals with a competitive skillset grounded in healthcare informatics   Apply            Health Information Management Programs  The need for specialists in electronic patient records continues to increase. Our on-campus and online health information management programs provide skilled instruction in the collection, management and use of information in healthcare systems, and prepare you to take the Registered Health Information Administrator (RHIA) exam.  NOTICE: The IBHE Post-baccalaureate Certificate in Health Information Management will transition to a Master of Science in Health Information Management in fall 2020, pending approval of the University of Illinois Board of Trustees and Illinois Board of Higher Education. Once the MS is approved, no new enrollments will be permitted in the certificate program. Currently enrolled certificate students will have the option to complete the certificate or change to the MS degree. Students completing requirements for either program will be eligible for the RHIA exam, but there will be a delay for graduates of the MS degree until the program receives CAHIIM accreditation, which is anticipated to be within one year of the first graduating class.   Request information       Name  Type  Description  Apply       BS in Health Information Management   On Campus or Online  Take the first step in becoming an expert in safeguarding critical and private patient data   Apply      Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Information Management   Online  Expand on your bachelor’s degree and get a solid foundation in using technology to manage healthcare data   Apply           What makes us great            Full online access to the UIC Library of the Health Sciences  Library materials include 61,000 journal titles, monographs and audiovisual materials on medicine, nursing, pharmacology and other health professions      Learn more about the library              Sam Bond  Teaches interactive visualization and helps students understand the power of drawing in learning anatomical content      Sam's profile              Qualify to take the RHIA exam  Our accredited HIM programs prepare students for the Registered Health Information Administrators (RHIA) exam administered by the American Health Information Management Association      Find out more about HIM              Andrew Boyd  Researching data simplification to improve clinical outcomes and transforming the electronic health record system to engage patients in their own care      Andrew's profile              Health Informatics Practicum  Work with a preceptor to gain experience and earn course credit through the Health Informatics Practicum      Find out what to expect              Lois Hitchcock  A Fellow of the American Health Information Management Association and leading expert in healthcare management and business practices      Lois' profile                Recent News     Art, science come together in life science visualization minor   Wednesday, February 12, 2020      UIC climbs to No. 3 in U.S. News Best Online Programs rankings   Tuesday, January 14, 2020     Miriam Isola to be inducted as a fellow in the American Medical Informatics Association   Monday, December 2, 2019     Ashley Hughes receives the 2019 Bentzi Karsh Early-Career Service Award from the Human Factors and Ergonomics Society   Monday, December 2, 2019     Medical alarms may be inaudible to hospital staff   Tuesday, October 22, 2019      All BHIS news             Biomedical and Health Information Sciences    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          BS in Health Information Management    Expand BS in Health Information Management menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      Minor in Life Science Visualization    Expand Minor in Life Science Visualization menu          What to Expect    Applying      MS in Biomedical Visualization    Expand MS in Biomedical Visualization menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Meet Our Students    Expand Meet Our Students menu          Class of 2020    Class of 2021        MS in Health Informatics    PhD 